                            <comment id="141913" author="adilger" created="Wed, 10 Feb 2016 23:26:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The sanity-lfsck interop problems are unrelated to this ticket I think?   In any case, we have completely disabled interop testing with lfsck (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7144&quot; title=&quot;Interop 2.7.0&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;master- sanity-scrub test_14: (6) Some entry under /lost+found should be repaired&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7144&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7144&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) because this is purely server-side functionality and there isn&apos;t any value testing this with different client versions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As previously mentioned, the ost-pools test failure is due to&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/13241&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/13241&lt;/a&gt; and will continue to fail interop testing until that patch is landed to 2.5.x or the tests are skipped.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
